tool_description: Human-readable text comparisons, 2 and 3-way diff, merge and more.
name: Treediff
title: Treediff

api_list.name: merge
api_list.description:
Request the 3-way merge between a `head`, a `compare` and a `base` value.
The `base` value serves as the "common ancestor".
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://treediff.p.rapidapi.com/merge"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "treediff.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: diff
api_list.description:
Request diffs between a `head` and a `compare` and optional `base` value.
Adding a `base` param triggers the 3-way diff with `base` as the "common ancestor".
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://treediff.p.rapidapi.com/diff"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "treediff.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
